{
  "doc_id": "7471",
  "text": "Aluminium chloride method was used in determination of the concentrations of flavonoids [CITATION_1] . The preparation of samples was performed in triplicate and the mean value of absorbance was calculated. Rutin was used as a standard for calibration of standard curve. The linear equation of standard curve (y = 0.021x + 0.040, R2 = 0.999) was used in calculating the concentrations of total flavonoids. Finally, the concentrations of total flavonoids were shown by form -milligram of rutin equivalent per gram of extract (mg of RU/g of extract).",
